{"actor":{"display":"Evin Tunador","id":"evintunador@gmail.com","type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":"1:# Conversation Ledger\n2:\n3:Durable, attributable records of visible coding-agent conversations, stored in\n4:your repository as git notes.\n5:\n6:`cledger` (also installed as `conversation-ledger`) is a small standalone\n7:utility in the unix tradition: it appends immutable JSONL evidence events to\n8:`refs/notes/conversation-ledger`, anchored to the commit you were on when the\n9:conversation happened. Records ride the commit DAG — merge a branch and its\n10:conversations come along — never touch your working tree or `git status`, and\n11:ride your normal `git push`/`git fetch` via an auto-installed, scan-gated\n12:pre-push hook and fetch refspec (or explicitly, via `cledger sync`).\n13:\n14:Conversation Ledger is the neutral foundation of a small ecosystem:\n15:\n16:- `conversation-ledger` stores normalized, provenance-preserving conversation evidence.\n17:- `turnbridge` records and transfers visible conversations between coding CLIs.\n18:- `intent-recall` later retrieves evidence to help agents reason about original and superseded intent.\n19:\n20:The ledger itself never summarizes, ranks, or interprets. It stores what was\n21:visibly said, by whom, against which commit — nothing more.\n22:\n23:## Install\n24:\n25:```sh\n26:git clone https://github.com/evintunador/conversation-ledger\n27:cd conversation-ledger && npm install && npm link   # npm publish coming later\n28:cledger install all    # hook capture into Claude Code + Codex CLI\n29:```\n30:\n31:`cledger install` adds `Stop`/`SessionEnd` hooks to `~/.claude/settings.json`\n32:and a `Stop` hook (plus `features.hooks = true`) to `~/.codex/config.toml`,\n33:backing both up first. From then on, every completed turn in any git\n34:repository is captured automatically, in the same universal format. Capture is\n35:idempotent — events are content-derived, so re-scanning a transcript never\n36:duplicates.\n37:\n38:Two one-time activation notes: Claude Code reads hooks at session start, so\n39:capture begins with your next session; Codex requires you to trust new hooks\n40:interactively — open `codex`, run `/hooks`, and approve the `cledger hook\n41:codex` command once. Missed turns are never lost either way: `cledger capture\n42:<source> --transcript PATH` backfills any native transcript, idempotently.\n43:\n44:## Use\n45:\n46:```sh\n47:cledger log                     # events on the current branch (via commit reachability)\n48:cledger log --all --json        # every event, as JSONL for jq & friends\n49:cledger conversations           # sessions touching this branch\n50:cledger show claude-code:3f9a   # replay one conversation in order\n51:cledger export > ledger.jsonl   # lossless dump, incl. source-native payloads\n52:cledger sync                    # explicit fetch/merge/push of the ledger ref\n53:echo '{\"kind\":\"decision\",...}' | cledger append   # any tool can write events\n54:```\n55:\n90:   sync` (the E scan gates the push either way — see \"Transport\").\n91:\n92:Events captured before the first commit exists (unborn `HEAD`) queue in\n93:`.git/conversation-ledger/pending.jsonl` and flush into the first real\n94:anchor. Everything under `.git/conversation-ledger/` (pending queue, adapter\n95:cursors, lock) is local, rebuildable state — never the record of truth.\n96:\n97:### Known limitation: squash merges\n98:\n99:A squash merge discards the source branch's commits, so their conversations\n100:remain in the ledger (notes are enumerable regardless of reachability;\n101:`cledger log --all` sees them) but drop out of the target branch's\n102:reachability view. A future `re-anchor` operation is the intended fix.\n103:\n104:## Transport\n105:\n106:Default-on, wired by the first capture in a repo (`ensureTransport`, run on\n107:every append as cheap re-checks so a remote added later still gets covered;\n108:never throws — it runs inside capture):\n109:\n110:- **Push half.** A `pre-push` hook calls `cledger transport-push <remote>`,\n111:  which pushes the ledger ref gated by the layer-E scan. Policy: a finding\n112:  holds back *only the ledger* — secrets never leave the machine, but a\n113:  false positive never blocks shipping code; `{\"transport\": {\"strict\":\n114:  true}}` escalates to aborting the entire push. Any other failure warns\n115:  and lets the push proceed. Installation is chain-safe: append to an\n116:  existing shell hook, back off with a one-time warning when\n117:  `core.hooksPath` or a non-shell hook owns the file. The hook script\n118:  embeds the installing cledger's absolute node+cli.js path (PATH fallback\n119:  in the script), treats \"cledger gone\" as success, and a\n120:  `CLEDGER_INTERNAL` env guard (set by `sync` around its own push) stops\n121:  the ledger push from re-triggering the hook.\n122:- **Fetch half.** A `+refs/notes/conversation-ledger:refs/notes/\n123:  cledger-incoming` refspec on `origin` makes plain `git fetch`/`git pull`\n124:  stage the remote's ref; `absorbIncoming` folds the staging ref into the\n125:  local ref lazily at read time (every `readEvents`) via the same\n126:  `cat_sort_uniq` union — absorption can only add events, and the local\n127:  ref is never force-overwritten. `cledger sync`'s fetch phase uses the\n128:  identical staging path.\n129:- **Opt-out.** `{\"transport\": {\"hook\": false, \"fetchRefspec\": false}}`\n130:  (config), or delete the marked hook block. `cledger sync` stays available\n131:  regardless.\n132:\n133:## Capture adapters\n134:\n135:`cledger install` registers per-turn hooks globally: Claude Code","is_error":false,"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WdrcnMy41hmEXrxB2anCS7","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","head":"5581e317b1b9c3ea88c5d9dd25808a10fcfc7518","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:4c1